The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 28: The rate of inflation shot up marginally to 4.71 per cent for the week ended October 15 from 4.62 per cent in the previous week mainly because of increase in the prices of essential food, non-food, minerals and manufacturing items. However, it was still lower than 7.21 per cent a year ago. Spiralling prices of onion along with moderate rise in prices of other vegetables, fruits and edible oils due to festival demand burnt holes in the pockets of consumers. Wholesale price index inched up by 0.3 per cent to 197.7 points for the week.

 New Delhi, Oct. 28: The Company Law Board (CLB) today adjourned the hearing on allotment of shares to IOC in Haldia Petrochemicals Ltd to November 21. After hearing the case for three days, CLB principal bench headed by chairman S. Balasubramanian posted the matter for November 21-25.

 Mumbai, Oct. 28: The RBI has extended the reduction in benchmark prime lending rate for rupee export credit by six months till April 2006.

 Mumbai, Oct. 28: Indian Airlines has re-launched the super-saver scheme and introduced two innovative facilities for booking ? dial-a-ticket and IA-IDBI ATM ticketing as festive bonanza. 

 Chandigarh, Oct. 28: Hong Kong-based Distacom has sold its stake in the BK Modi-promoted Spice Telecom to Ashmore Investment Management Ltd and the Deutsche Bank group.




